{
  "texts": [
    "Naively, when a cluster is expanded, the whole layout needs to be recalculated because now the cluster sequence is changed.",
    "To avoid such recalculation, we design our spacing strategy in this way so that the sub-clusters can simply take over the space of their parent cluster, as shown in Figure 4.",
    "Since the total volume of the sub-clusters is the size of the parent cluster and the space is proportional, the subclusters can take over exactly the space of the parent cluster without any overflow or underflow.",
    "This ensures a local change in the layout when a cluster is expanded.3) Concave Hull Approximation: After applying the SFC layout, we use a concave hull algorithm [44] to generate an approximation polygon for each cluster.",
    "The polygons are used to generate borders and calculate label positions for the clusters."
  ]
}